    "description": "A mountain in modern Turkey's İzmir province that was probably known as \"Olympos\" in antiquity.",
    "details": "<p>The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: Nif Dağı. The <a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"resolveuid/95e2ec4847914a69a1042af7ff606705\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\">Karabel pass</a> on the southern side of Mt. Nif leads toward the modern town of Torbalı and is noted for <a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"resolveuid/0534b96e39b94bf398484077553c6b3b\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\">a series of Hittite rock-cut reliefs with Luwian inscriptions</a>.</p>",
